      "content": "wait, if you mock everything, doesn't that mean we aren't actually testing the real app? i need these tests to be \"comprehensive\" like i asked so we know the app works. if the auth service is actually broken in production, mocked tests won't catch it. can you write them to actually hit the real endpoints but just make them stable enough to hit that 100% pass rate? the goal is to confirm the flow works without the flakiness crashing the build.",
